==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|therfore}}, {{m|enm|therfor}}, {{m|enm|tharfore}}, {{m|enm|thorfore}}; synchronically a {{univ|en|there|pos1=pronomial adverb|for|nocap=1|lit=for that (reason)}}. The spelling has been changed due to a reanalysis as {{m|en|there}} + {{m|en|fore||lit=forward from that; [[thence]]}}. See also {{m|en|therefor}}, ultimately the same formation.

Compare {{cog|stq|deerfoar}}, {{cog|nl|daarvoor}}, {{cog|de|dafür}}, {{cog|da|-}} and {{cog|no|derfor}}, {{cog|sv|därför}}.

